What is the ISM Purchasing Managers Index (MFG Survey) and how is it calculated?

The ISM Purchasing Managers Index (MFG Survey) is a monthly report compiled by the Institute for Supply Management in the United States. It is based on data collected from purchasing and supply executives across the country. The index measures the change, if any, in various indicators compared to the previous month, such as new orders, production, employment, and prices. The report shows the percentage of respondents reporting each response, the net difference between positive and negative responses, and a diffusion index that reflects the prevailing direction of change. The index is calculated by considering the percentage of positive responses plus half of those responding the same.
